<item>
            <title>[SOLR-310] Deleting pending handling can cause OOM</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-310</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Mike:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Could happen when doDeleting the pending docs too.  James: try&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt;&amp;gt; sending commit every 500k docs or so.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yonik:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; Hmmm, right... some of the memory usage will be related to the treemap&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; keeping track of deleted items, and some of it will be related to the&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; reader itself (the term index, and the norms).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;gt; Perhaps we should have some sort of limit on the number of deletions&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;gt; we cache so people don&apos;t have to worry about that part.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Good idea.  Perhaps a solrconfig.xml setting, &amp;lt;maxPendingDocs&amp;gt;?  Default to 100k?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
